Welcome back to Wall Power, coming to you from Frieze Los Angeles.
I=E2=80=99m Marion Maneker.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

It=E2=80=99s still early in the week, but by the time you read this, I=E2=
=80=99ll have already been through a few openings and started to get the la=
y of the land here at Frieze. The main action doesn=E2=80=99t get underway =
until Wednesday and Thursday, however, so by Friday I should have a lot mor=
e for you from L.A. Tonight, I=E2=80=99m going to turn it over to Julie Dav=
ich to
tell the fascinating story of the growing market for the work of the jazz w=
itch, Gertrude Abercrombie.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* Getting Tillmans right: Almost immediately after sending Sunday=E2=80=99s=
 newsletter, I received a note from a close follower of Wolfgang Tillmans=
=E2=80=99 market, asking me to clear up my comment that Tillmans=E2=80=99 p=
rices peaked five years ago, with few recent sales above $100,000. Alas, I =
hadn=E2=80=99t been using the ARTDAI dataset properly=E2=80=94I=E2=80=99d b=
een looking only at unique images, instead of Tillmans=E2=80=99 editioned w=
ork. So let me clarify: The top auction price for a work by Tillmans peaked=
 in
2017 at nearly $800,000. That year was also the peak for total dollar volum=
e at auction for the photographer=E2=80=99s work, at just above $10 million=
=2E Since then, one work sold for aroun=
d $500,000 (in 2020), only four works=20=
sold for more than $240,000 (in 2023), and just two sold above $160,000 las=
t year.

At the same time, more lots by Tillmans were sold during each of the past f=
our years than in 2017. The point I was trying to make with the unique data=
 stands for the full dataset:
Bidders are acquiring more lower-value works by Tillmans, which is reflecte=
d in the collection that Christie=E2=80=99s is going to sell in March. Ther=
e is one work estimated at =C2=A3120,000, and the remaining works are all e=
stimated in the low five figures=E2=80=94the sweet spot in Tillmans=E2=80=
=99 market. If you want to do your own research using ARTDAI=E2=80=99s data=
