Banksy at Sotheby=E2=80=99s
---------------------

Mark Hoppus with Banksy=E2=80=99s Crude Oil (Vettriano)

Mark Hoppus with Banksy=E2=80=99s Crude Oil
(Vettriano). Photo: Max Montgomery

Mark Hoppus, of Blink-182 fame, is selling his
Banksy painting, Crude Oil (Vettriano), to fund a variety of charities incl=
uding California Fire Foundation, the Child Life Program at Children=E2=80=
=99s Hospital Los Angeles, and oncology research at Cedars-Sinai. The paint=
ing riffs on the most famous image of self-taught painter Jack Vettriano, o=
ne of Britain=E2=80=99s most popular artists. The work will be sold at Soth=
eby=E2=80=99s in London this March with a =C2=A33 million estimate.

=C2=A0

Originally shown at Banksy=E2=80=99s milestone event in 2005, the work is o=
ne of a series of paintings the artist called =E2=80=9Ccrude oils.=E2=80=9D=
 Each work takes a famous painting by another artist, including Monet and v=
an Gogh, and remixes it with more realistic (in Banksy=E2=80=99s view) upda=
tes. Vettriano=E2=80=99s inclusion in the series is as much a commentary on=
 the elitism of the art world as it is a satire of our degraded
environment.

